; ADP wire-format — agent-only files
; v1.1 — minimize tokens for session→session communication

purpose
 minimize tokens
 no human in loop
 prose stays in @../docs/  ; for human/onboarding/debug
 wire is for active work between sessions

files
 proc.wire     process rules ; ~280 tok (vs ~5300 markdown)
 roles.wire    role defs     ; ~250 tok (vs ~4300 markdown)
 dispatch.wire who-does-what ; ~150 tok (vs ~770 markdown)
 tasks.wire    task index    ; ~30 tok/task (vs ~500 markdown/task)
 results.jsonl append-log    ; ~40 tok/event
 status        one-liner state per role

syntax
 ; comment
 KEY value           single field
 KEY=value           inline
 SECTION
  field val           indented child
 @path               file-ref (cwd=.adp/)
 @path#anchor        sub-ref
 @path:Ln-Lm         line-range
 →                   flow (arrow)
 ≤≥                  bounds
 lists space-sep     ; "P0 P1 P2 P3"

read-order on session start
 1 @proc.wire        ; 280 tok
 2 @roles.wire       ; 250 tok — pick your row
 3 @dispatch.wire    ; 150 tok — what to do now
 4 @tasks.wire       ; grep your role's tasks ; 30 tok/match
 5 @plans/...        ; only for tasks you take
 total ~700-900 tok startup vs ~7700 prose ; ~9x compression

write rules
 arch writes dispatch.wire tasks.wire (status fields only)
 anyone appends results.jsonl
 status one-liner self-updated by each role on take/complete
 prose docs/ stay canonical for humans ; wire derived
 reconcile arch runs ./scripts/wire-sync.sh end-of-session

trust
 wire is truth for "right now"
 prose is truth for "how to think about it"
 conflict → arch resolves ; updates wire from prose
